column1: Rate of COVID-19 Cases per 100,000 Population by Age Group and Week of First Positive Test Date

Source: Rhode Island Department of Health (RIDOH) SalesForce COVID-19 Case Dataset; US Census Bureau 2018 annual estimates by single year of age (population by age group) and 2018 American Community Survey 5-year estimates (total population).

NOTES: Congregate setting residents are included. Out-of-state residents are excluded. 
Data reflect number of people who tested positive (rather than number of test results). Rates based on small numbers (<5) are shown as *, in line with RIDOH's Small Numbers Policy. We provide weekly data to help show broader trends over time. Fluctuations in these data may be due to a variety of factors, such as cyclical testing. Please use caution when interpreting these data. Risk is associated with the characteristics of settings and behaviors of people, not necessarily with age group.
